  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Comprehensive legislation defining money laundering offenses\n- Mandatory reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Establishing regulatory bodies to monitor financial transactions\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Requiring suspicious transaction reporting\n- Implementing customer due diligence procedures\n- Establishing penalties and enforcement mechanisms\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance Requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Regular risk assessments\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Financial penalties\n- International cooperation\n\n6. Specific Reporting Obligations\n- Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n- Currency Transaction Reports\n- Cross-border transfer declarations\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining the integrity of global financial systems.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
